bug.author: wschin
bug.description:
All Azure CIs fail for some unknown reasons in <denchmark-link:https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/2966>#2966</denchmark-link> and some other PRs. Here is a screenshot for the status. <denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3524474/91211185-33c85680-e6c3-11ea-997d-880a8a0131e6.png></denchmark-link>
If we look into its log, we can see some missing definitions like <denchmark-code>onnx/__init__.py:104: error: Name 'ModelProto' is not defined onnx/__init__.py:129: error: Name 'TensorProto' is not defined onnx/__init__.py:144: error: Name 'ModelProto' is not defined onnx/__init__.py:155: error: Name 'ModelProto' is not defined onnx/__init__.py:158: error: Name 'TensorProto' is not defined onnx/__init__.py:169: error: Name 'TensorProto' is not defined onnx/__init__.py:172: error: Name 'ModelProto' is not defined </denchmark-code>
Since Travis Linux CIs are all passed and that PR was good before sync with master, I guess Azure CIs might have some problems.

comments.comment: Hi <denchmark-link:https://github.com/wschin>@wschin</denchmark-link> , I encounter the same error in my PR. Even if I rerun the master commit, it will also encounter this error. The error occurs here in Linux CIs: . I am digging into this issue. Thank you for reporting this.
It has been fixed in <denchmark-link:https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/2974>#2974</denchmark-link> . Thank you.
